Power cuts on the Queen Mary 2 left the ocean liner without propulsion in the North Pacific.

The ship, which has more than 2,600 passengers and 1,000 crew on board, was left without electricity during two power cuts within days of each other. One incident happened as the ship sailed from Australia to Japan.

